headline: T. Rowe Price (TROW) Earnings Rebound Challenges Bearish Narratives on Value and Profitability
summary: T. Rowe Price Group (TROW) reported a 4.7% increase in earnings over the past year, reversing a five-year stretch of declining results that averaged 9.1% per year. Profit margins also nudged higher, with net profit margin improving to 28% from 27.9%. Shares are trading at $102.53, well below the estimated fair value of $168.35. Investors are seeing reasons for optimism in the company’s attractive valuation and a return to earnings growth, though longer-term growth projections remain more...
